	<logo>https://static.globalissues.org/i/globalissues/logo-feed.jpg</logo><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327</id><title>General Assembly approves $5.4 billion UN peacekeeping budget for 2025-2026</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;The General Assembly on Monday approved a $5.38 billion budget for UN peacekeeping operations for the 2025-2026 fiscal year, down slightly from the previous year, as delegates wrapped up weeks of negotiations amid warnings about persistent funding challenges.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40327&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “General Assembly approves $5.4 billion UN peacekeeping budget for 2025-2026”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326</id><title>Gaza: Families deprived of the means for survival, humanitarians warn</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The United Nations on Tuesday reported that humanitarian operations in Gaza are facing escalating strain, as ongoing fuel shortages, access restrictions and military activity continue to undermine aid delivery and essential services. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40326&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: Families deprived of the means for survival, humanitarians warn”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/26-06-2025-UNRWA-Gaza-07.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325</id><title>Sudan: UN warns of soaring displacement and looming floods</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;UN humanitarians on Tuesday sounded the alarm over worsening humanitarian conditions in Sudan, as escalating violence continues to displace civilians and the rising risk of severe flooding during the current rainy season. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40325&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Sudan: UN warns of soaring displacement and looming floods”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/08-04-2025-UNOCHA-Sudan-12.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40324</id><title>Children’s lives ‘turned upside down’ by wars across Middle East, North Africa, warns UNICEF</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40324" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/25-06-2025-UNICEF-child_school.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/25-06-2025-UNICEF-child_school.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Conflicts in the Middle East and North Africa in the last two years reportedly killed, maimed, or displaced over 12 million children across the region, according to the UN Children’s Fund (UNICEF).&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40324&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Children’s lives ‘turned upside down’ by wars across Middle East, North Africa, warns UNICEF”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/25-06-2025-UNICEF-child_school.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40323</id><title>Iran crisis: UN stays and delivers</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40323" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/13-06-2025_UN_Iran.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/13-06-2025_UN_Iran.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;A clearer picture of needs across Iran is beginning to emerge after the conflict this month with Israel, which left hundreds dead, several hospitals hit and a spike in Afghan refugees returning home, the UN’s top official in Tehran said on Tuesday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40323&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Iran crisis: UN stays and delivers”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/13-06-2025_UN_Iran.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40322</id><title>‘The margins of the budget’: Gender equality in developing countries underfunded by $420 billion annually</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40322" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/11-06-2025-UNICEF-gender-equality.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/11-06-2025-UNICEF-gender-equality.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Developing countries currently face a staggering $420 billion annual gap in the funding needed to achieve gender equality, UN Women estimates. This gap means that programmes and services for women and girls are chronically underfunded.  &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40322&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “‘The margins of the budget’: Gender equality in developing countries underfunded by $420 billion annually”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/11-06-2025-UNICEF-gender-equality.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40321</id><title>50 years of CITES: Shielding wildlife from trade-driven extinction</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40321" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/14-05-2024-UN_News-Tiger.JPG/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/14-05-2024-UN_News-Tiger.JPG/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The Convention on International Trade in Endangered Species of Wild Fauna and Flora (CITES) marks 50 years since it entered into force on Tuesday, celebrating five decades of protecting endangered wildlife from overexploitation through international trade. &lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40321&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “50 years of CITES: Shielding wildlife from trade-driven extinction”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/14-05-2024-UN_News-Tiger.JPG/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40320</id><title>Spain and Brazil push global action to tax the super-rich and curb inequality</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40320" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/01-07-2025_Unsplash_yacht.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/01-07-2025_Unsplash_yacht.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Spain and Brazil have launched a joint initiative to promote a higher tax take from the super-rich worldwide, aiming to tackle soaring inequality by ensuring those with the most, pay their fair share.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40320&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Spain and Brazil push global action to tax the super-rich and curb inequality”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/01-07-2025_Unsplash_yacht.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40319</id><title>Northern hemisphere heatwave underscores value of early-warning alerts</title><updated>2025-07-01T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40319" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/02-08-2024-WHO-heat.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/02-08-2024-WHO-heat.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The blistering early-summer heatwave that’s brought life-threatening temperatures across much of the northern hemisphere is a worrying sign of things to come, UN weather experts said on Tuesday.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/07/01/40319&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Northern hemisphere heatwave underscores value of early-warning alerts”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Collections/Embargoed/02-08-2024-WHO-heat.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry><entry><id>https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318</id><title>Gaza: UN urges Israel to allow fuel into Strip</title><updated>2025-06-30T05:00:00-07:00</updated><link rel="alternate" type="text/html" href="https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318" /><link rel="enclosure" type="image/jpg" href="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg" /><summary type="html">&lt;p&gt;&lt;img src=&quot;https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image1170x530cropped.jpg&quot; width=&quot;640&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The crisis in Gaza is worsening, UN humanitarians warned on Monday, as ongoing hostilities and access restrictions drive displaced communities deeper into despair.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.globalissues.org/news/2025/06/30/40318&quot;&gt;Read the full story, “Gaza: UN urges Israel to allow fuel into Strip”, on globalissues.org&lt;/a&gt; →&lt;/p&gt;</summary><media:thumbnail url="https://global.unitednations.entermediadb.net/assets/mediadb/services/module/asset/downloads/preset/Libraries/Production%20Library/31-05-2024_UN%20News_%20Gaza%20Port%201.jpg/image100x100cropped.jpg" width="100" height="100" /></entry></feed><!-- 0.0009s -->